hu.elte.txtuml.api

Interface Collection<T extends ModelClass>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of model objects to be contained in this collection
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Association.HiddenMany, Association.HiddenMaybeOne, Association.HiddenOne, Association.HiddenSome, Association.Many, Association.MaybeOne, Association.One, Association.Some, AssociationEnd, Collection.Empty

    public interface Collection<T extends ModelClass>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Base interface for immutable collections of ModelClass objects.

    Represents: collection of model objects

    Usage:

    After getting an object which implements this interface, call its methods anywhere from the model where action code or condition evaluation is written.

    See the documentation of Model for details about the action language and condition evaluations in the model.

    Java restrictions:

    • Define subtype: disallowed, use its predefined subclasses instead, like Collection.Empty or AssociationEnd

    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.

    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs
    See Also:
    Collection.Empty, AssociationEnd
